📋 Session 2026-07-17 (release-drift-gates: brainstorm → SPEC → plan):
- PR #149 (main, merged): BRAINSTORM + SPEC for two gaps found while shipping #143/#147 — no
  gate catches a formula content change with no version/revision bump; `.STATUS` can silently
  hold unresolved git conflict markers. SPEC scoped to a revision-drift CI check + a `.STATUS`
  conflict-marker guard; deferred a `/craft:release`-side pre-flight variant and an age-based
  `.STATUS` staleness threshold as open questions.
- PR #150 (main, merged): corrected the SPEC's integration point — reuse the existing
  `formula-drift.yml` ("Formula Drift Guard") workflow (already triggers on `generator/**` +
  `Formula/**`, already runs `check-drift.sh`'s regen+diff pattern) instead of proposing a new
  workflow.
- Adversarial review of the SPEC surfaced two real gaps neither draft had caught: `main` has no
  `required_status_checks` at all (guardrails-only protection, documented tradeoff for
  `update-formula.yml`'s `auto_merge: true`) — so a failing gate wouldn't actually block a
  merge; and `formula-drift.yml`'s `actions/checkout@v4` has no `fetch-depth` override (default
  shallow clone), so the planned base-ref diff can't run without a fix first.
- PR #151 (main, merged 8a8273b): `tasks/plan.md` + `tasks/todo.md` — 10-task, 5-phase
  breakdown incorporating both review findings (Task 1 fixes fetch-depth before any diff logic;
  Phase 3's checkpoint makes the required-status-checks decision an explicit human gate).
  Cosmetic-only escape hatch resolved as a `revision-exempt` PR label (per-PR scoped, no
  standing manifest flag to forget). Code review of the plan itself found one further gap not
  yet folded in: the label doesn't survive to the `push`-triggered re-run after a squash-merge,
  so an exempted change could show a false-failure red X on `main` post-merge — needs an
  acceptance-criterion fix to Task 4 before implementing it.
- Nothing implemented yet — Tasks 1-10 are still open. Next real work is driving Task 1.

📋 Session 2026-07-16 (folio-install silent registration failure fix):
- PR #143 (main, merged 5c08475, squash, branch deleted): folio's
  `generator/manifest.json` entry had no `"features"` key at all, so
  `generate.py` silently omitted both the marketplace.json-mirroring block
  and the `CLAUDE_RUNNING` detection block from `Formula/folio.rb` — `brew
  install` reported success but never registered folio with Claude Code
  (Data-Wise/folio#18). Fix: added `features.marketplace` +
  `features.claude_detection` to folio's manifest entry, regenerated
  `Formula/folio.rb` (not hand-edited) — `--diff` confirmed all other 6
  formulas byte-identical. Added `tests/test_manifest_required_features.sh`
  as a structural guard (verified red against the pre-fix manifest, green
  after); documented the required-flags convention in CLAUDE.md's Formula
  Generator section (same doc gap that let this ship unnoticed).
- Spec: folio repo's `docs/specs/SPEC-fix-install-registration-2026-07-16.md`.
- folio#18 auto-closed on merge ("Fixes #18" in PR body); confirmation comment posted.
- Worktree `feature-fix-folio-install` removed, local + remote branch deleted (merged, no orphan).
- Follow-up PR #147 (main, merged dcecd5c, squash, branch deleted): #143 fixed the install
  script but never bumped version/revision, so `brew upgrade` couldn't detect the change on
  already-installed folio 1.0.0 — only an explicit `brew reinstall` picked it up. Added generator
  support for an optional `revision` manifest field (emitted as `revision N` after `license`);
  set `revision: 1` on folio's entry. Verified live twice: (1) copied the regenerated formula
  into the local tap checkout pre-merge — `brew outdated` correctly flagged folio; (2) after
  merge, plain `brew update` pulled the change and `brew outdated` showed
  `data-wise/tap/folio` without any manual copy — confirms the real propagation path works, not
  just the local test.
- Separately observed during manual `brew reinstall` testing: the post_install marketplace-sync
  retry (PR #134, 2 attempts/1s apart) still lost the race on a real run — degraded to the
  advisory fallback as designed, not a crash, but flagged as a follow-up (background task
  `task_5812724d`, tracked outside this repo's session).

📋 Session 2026-07-02 (post_install marketplace-sync race fix):
- PR #134 (main, merged): post_install Step 3 (`claude plugin marketplace update
  local-plugins`) fired immediately after Step 2's `Process.waitpid` returned,
  before the spawned install script's marketplace-mirror write was guaranteed
  visible — spurious "Marketplace 'local-plugins' not found" on `brew reinstall`
  even though the manifest was correct (reproduced live during a craft v2.58.0
  reinstall check; standalone re-runs of the exact command succeeded every time,
  confirming a transient post_install-subprocess race, not a config problem).
  Fix: retry the marketplace-update call once with a 1s delay; degrade to an
  advisory `opoo` with the manual fix-it command if both attempts fail;
  `plugin update` now gated on a successful sync (previously fired unconditionally).
  Fixed in `generator/generate.py` (never hand-edited into `.rb` files); all 6
  claude-plugin formulas (craft, himalaya-mcp, scholar, rforge,
  rforge-orchestrator, workflow) regenerated — `brew audit --strict` clean,
  `ruby -c` clean, existing `test_no_symlink_install.sh` green. New
  `tests/test_marketplace_sync_resilience.sh` added, verified via planted-defect
  positive control (5/5 checks correctly failed on the old pattern, restored to
  green on the fix) before merge. CI (Regen vs committed drift guard) green,
  merged clean, `main` synced locally.
- Also fixed: local checkout was stuck on stale branch
  `fix/craft-command-count-116` (its PR #133 was already squash-merged) —
  switched to `main`, pulled, confirmed 0 unmerged work lost.
- Worktree `feature-post-install-marketplace-resilience` created and removed
  same session (merged, no orphan left).

